<TITLE> Stocks rally on buying spree </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)Stocks rallied Tuesday after a period of losses as investors bought heavily into banks, pharmaceuticals, mutual funds and financial institutions. Meanwhile, some investors sold power issues to lock in profits, according to brokerage house officials. "We had to deal with a lot of buying orders from our clients in almost every sector, sell-offs for profit-taking was very low today," an official of brokerage house IDLC Securities told bdnews24.com. Analysts termed the day's trade "a positive sign for the market" following two days of price corrections. "Investors are behaving rationally; after two days of profit-taking they are now engaged in mass buying, which is a healthy sign," Dhaka Stock Exchange chief executive Salahuddin Ahmed told bdnews24.com. The DSE general index steadily gained throughout the day to end 27.97 points up, or 0.92 percent, closing on 3068.57. The DSI or all share price index finished at 2581.97, up 22.65 points, or 0.88 percent. The DSE-20 blue chip index rose 16.63 points, or 0.71 percent, to close at 2332.77. Turnover rose to Tk 3.24 billion from 31,363,365 traded shares. Gainers outnumbered losers 154 to 88, with nine issues holding steady. AB Bank topped the turnover board, closing at Tk 3564, up 3.36 percent. AIMS 1st Mutual Fund followed, continuing its advance from Monday, to end on Tk 12.57, up 6.25 percent. Square Pharmaceuticals also continued its gains from the previous day, rising 2.47 percent to close at Tk 4593.75. IFIC Bank eroded Sunday's losses to end on Tk 2905, up 0.66 percent. Power Grid Company of Bangladesh fell on profit-taking, closing 0.07 percent lower at Tk 675.50. Among other scrips on the turnover board: Grameen Mutual Fund One, Uttara Bank and Lanka Bangla Finance advanced. Union Capitals and Beximco Pharma fell. All indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also ended higher, influenced by gains in insurance, paper and mutual funds. The CSCX or selective categories index closed at 5501.06, advancing 44.71 points or 0.81 percent. The CASPI or all-share price index rose 66.11 points, or 0.78 percent, to end on 8493.10. The CSE-30 blue-chip index ended on 7389.22, up 64.62 points, or 0.88 percent to close at 7324.59. Turnover on the port city bourse rose slightly to Tk 463.62 million from 6,263,977 traded shares. Of the traded issues, 89 advanced, 56 declined and six held steady. bdn
